# PolicyCodex credentials. Lives on the host at:
#   ~/.config/policycodex/config.env
# bind-mounted read-only into the container as /secrets/config.env.
# Copy this template there and fill in the values:
#   mkdir -p ~/.config/policycodex
#   cp config.env.example ~/.config/policycodex/config.env
#   <edit the copy with your real values>
#
# Format: POSIX KEY=VALUE per line. `#` starts a comment. Quotes optional.
# A malformed line is logged but does not block boot; well-formed lines up
# to the bad one still get exported.
#
# This file does NOT belong in Git. Anything you set here is a secret.

# --- GitHub App credentials (required to open PRs against your policy repo) ---
# Get these from the GitHub App you create per HOWTO-GitHub-Team-Setup.md.
# The private-key path MUST be a /secrets/... path (the host file at
# ~/.config/policycodex/github-app-private-key.pem appears at /secrets/...
# inside the container).
POLICYCODEX_GH_APP_ID=
POLICYCODEX_GH_INSTALLATION_ID=
POLICYCODEX_GH_PRIVATE_KEY_PATH=/secrets/github-app-private-key.pem

# --- LLM API key (one of the four; whichever you pick in wizard step 6) ---
# The provider SDKs read these env names directly, so no extra wiring is
# needed. Anthropic is the v0.1 default; uncomment the line for the
# provider you actually use and paste your key after the `=`.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=
# AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY=
